### Lightweight/Simple ERP (QuickBooks, Xero, etc.)
When system has **limited custom fields**, use structured description:
```
ITEM: CAB-012847-00
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

NAME: Cable Assy Power 47.5M
DESCRIPTION:
Cable Assembly, Power Distribution
- Length: 47.5M ± 0.1M
- Gauge: 18 AWG
- Type: Type X, Stranded copper
- Insulation: Black PVC
- Voltage: 600V
- Current: 10A
- Terminals: TERM-A crimped both ends
- Drawing: EE-12345-001 Rev B
- Spec: EE-SPEC-CABLE-001 Rev C
UOM: EA (each assembly)
Stock UOM: EA
Purchase UOM: N/A (make item)
VENDOR: Internal (fabricated)
COST: $17.50
CUSTOM FIELD 1 (Length): 47.5
CUSTOM FIELD 2 (Length_UOM): M
CUSTOM FIELD 3 (Drawing): EE-12345-001
```
## Searchability Strategy
With semantic-free part numbers, you need **strong search capabilities**:
### Multi-Field Search
```
SEARCH EXAMPLE: "Cable 47.5 meter"
Search fields:
├─ Part Number: CAB-012847-00 ❌ (no match)
├─ Description: "Cable Assembly..." ✓ (matches "cable")
├─ Attribute Length: 47.5 ✓ (exact match)
├─ Attribute Length_UOM: M ✓ (matches "meter")
└─ Drawing Number: EE-12345-001 ❌ (no match)

RESULT: CAB-012847-00 (high relevance)
```
### Parametric Search Interface
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  FIND PARTS                                 │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                             │
│  Category: [Cable Assembly ▼]              │
│                                             │
│  Length:   [47.5] [M ▼] ± [0.1]            │
│                                             │
│  Gauge:    [18 AWG ▼]                       │
│                                             │
│  Type:     [Type X ▼]                       │
│                                             │
│  Voltage:  [600V ▼]                         │
│                                             │
│  Status:   [✓] Active  [ ] Obsolete        │
│                                             │
│            [Search]  [Clear]                │
│                                             │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  RESULTS: 1 item found                      │
│                                             │
│  ☑ CAB-012847-00                            │
│     Cable Assembly, Power, 47.5M            │
│     18AWG, Type X, 600V                     │
│     Status: Released                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Intelligent Part Name Construction
Since part number is meaningless, **description becomes critical**:
```
PART NAME FORMULA (Auto-generated from attributes):
[Category] [Type] [Key_Param1] [Key_Param2] [Key_Param3]
Example:
Category: Cable Assembly
Type: Power
Length: 47.5M
Gauge: 18AWG
Voltage: 600V
GENERATED NAME:
"Cable Assy Power 47.5M 18AWG 600V"
Alternative format:
"Cable Assy, 47.5M, 18AWG, Type X, 600V"
Benefits:
- Human readable
- Contains searchable keywords
- Auto-updates if attributes change
- Consistent across all parts
```
## Managing Design Changes with Attributes
### Scenario: Length changes 47.5M → 49.8M

**Option 1: Create New Part Number (Recommended)**
```
OLD PART:
  PN: CAB-012847-00
  Status: Obsolete (superseded)
  Length: 47.5 M
  Superseded By: CAB-015921-00
  
NEW PART:
  PN: CAB-015921-00
  Status: Active
  Length: 49.8 M
  Supersedes: CAB-012847-00
  
REASON: Different functional length = different part
```
**Option 2: Revision Change (If length within tolerance)**
```
PART: CAB-012847-00
Rev A → Rev B

CHANGE:
  Attribute: Length_Tolerance
  Old: ± 0.1 M
  New: ± 0.5 M
  
REASON: Tolerance relaxation, same nominal length
```
## Attribute Naming Conventions
**Standardized attribute names** are critical:
```
NAMING STANDARD
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

Format: [Domain]_[Parameter]_[Qualifier]
Examples:
  DIM_Length_Nominal
  DIM_Length_Tolerance
  DIM_Length_Min
  DIM_Length_Max
  DIM_Diameter_Outer
  DIM_Width
  
  ELEC_Voltage_Rating
  ELEC_Current_Rating
  ELEC_Resistance
  
  MAT_Conductor_Type
  MAT_Insulation_Material
  
  MFG_Make_Buy
  MFG_Lead_Time
  
  UOM_Base
  UOM_Secondary
  UOM_Precision
Benefits:
- Alphabetically groups related attributes
- Clear domain ownership
- Supports reporting/analytics
- Consistent across system
```
## Workarounds for System Limitations
### If Custom Fields are Limited (< 10 fields)
**Priority Attributes:**
```
1. UDF_Length [decimal]        ← Most critical
2. UDF_Length_UOM [text]       ← Unit
3. UDF_Wire_Gauge [text]       ← Key spec
4. UDF_Cable_Type [text]       ← Identifier
5. UDF_Drawing_Num [text]      ← Reference
6. UDF_Status [list]           ← Lifecycle
7. UDF_Make_Buy [list]         ← Planning
8. UDF_Voltage [integer]       ← Safety critical
```

**Use structured description field for remaining data**
### If No Custom Fields Available
**Embed in description with parsing tags:**
```
DESCRIPTION:
Cable Assy, Power Distribution
[LEN:47.5M±0.1][GAUGE:18AWG][TYPE:X][VOLT:600V]
[DWG:EE-12345-001][SPEC:EE-SPEC-CABLE-001]
Stranded copper conductor, black PVC insulation
Crimp terminals both ends (TERM-A)
```
Can be parsed programmatically: `[TAG:VALUE]`
## Integration with Procurement
**Engineering attributes** must map to **procurement needs**:
```
ITEM: CAB-012847-00 (Engineering Part)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

ENGINEERING VIEW:
  Length Required: 47.5 M
  Base UOM: M
  Type: Make (fabricated)
  
PROCUREMENT VIEW (linked):
  Source Material: CAB-RAW-001 (bulk cable)
  Purchase UOM: EA (spool)
  Purchase Qty: 1 spool
  Spool Length: 50 M
  Utilization: 95%
  Waste: 2.5 M per assembly
  
LINKED ITEM: CAB-RAW-001
  Description: Cable Type X, bulk stock
  Purchase UOM: EA (spool)
  Purchase Size: 50 M per spool
  Supplier PN: ACME-CABLE-X-50M
  Unit Price: $250/spool
  Effective Cost: $5/M
This creates the translation layer between engineering specs and procurement reality, while keeping part numbers clean and attributes structured.
Summary: Best Practices
✅ DO:
• Use short, semantic-free part numbers
• Put ALL meaning in structured attributes
• Standardize attribute naming
• Auto-generate readable descriptions
• Enable parametric search
• Link engineering to procurement items
• Version control through ECO/revision
❌ DON'T:
• Encode dimensions in part number
• Exceed system character limits
• Use special characters that cause issues
• Rely on humans to parse encoded meanings
• Change part numbers for attribute changes (unless functionally different)
• Mix units in descriptions without clear labels
The key: Part numbers are database keys, attributes are data.
So how do we tag something like a cable that has a specific length for procurement to review it it's lens when the purchase length potentially is different. My not all buy items would have the issue. Like fasten have length but are purchased as an "each" item.
Tagging Items with Engineering vs. Procurement UOM Conflicts
This is a critical distinction - you need to flag items where the engineering UOM and procurement UOM are dimensionally incompatible, not just different.
The Key Distinction
No Conflict (Simple Conversion)
FASTENER EXAMPLE:
Engineering needs: 10 EA (10 bolts)
Procurement buys: 1 BX (box of 100 bolts)
Conversion: 1 BX = 100 EA
✓ Same dimension (count)
✓ Simple multiplication
✓ No waste issue
✓ No procurement review needed
```

### Has Conflict (Dimensional Mismatch)
```
CABLE EXAMPLE:
Engineering needs: 47.5 M (continuous length)
Procurement buys: 1 EA (spool containing 50M)
Conversion: 1 EA = 50 M, but...
⚠️ Different dimensions (count vs. length)
⚠️ Packaging constraint
⚠️ Potential waste
⚠️ REQUIRES procurement review
```

## Attribute Tags for Conflict Detection
### Primary Attribute: UOM_Conflict_Type
```
ITEM ATTRIBUTE: UOM_Conflict_Type
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

VALUES:
├─ "NONE" (default)
│   Engineering and procurement use compatible UOMs
│   Examples: Fasteners (EA to BX), resistors (EA to RL)
│
├─ "PACKAGING"
│   Different UOMs but straightforward conversion
│   Examples: Screws (EA to 100-packs), wire (M to spools)
│   Action: Auto-conversion, round up to package size
│
├─ "DIMENSIONAL"  ← KEY FLAG FOR YOUR USE CASE
│   Engineering specifies continuous dimension,
│   Procurement must buy discrete packages
│   Examples: Cable (length), sheet metal (area), pipe (length)
│   Action: REQUIRES procurement review and planning
│
├─ "CUT_TO_LENGTH"
│   Supplier offers cutting service at premium
│   Examples: Cable, tubing, extrusions
│   Action: Evaluate cut-to-length vs. standard packaging
│
└─ "BULK_MANAGED"
    Buy in bulk, cut/dispense internally
    Examples: Solder wire, adhesive tape, chain
    Action: Inventory management handles dispensing
```

### Supporting Attributes
```
DIMENSIONAL CONFLICT ATTRIBUTES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

UOM_Conflict_Type: DIMENSIONAL
Engineering_UOM: M (meter - continuous)
Engineering_Quantity: 47.5
Engineering_Tolerance: ± 0.1
Engineering_Dimension_Type: Length
Procurement_UOM: EA (each - discrete)
Procurement_Package_Size: 50 M per spool
Procurement_Package_Type: Spool
Procurement_Minimum_Order: 1 EA
Procurement_Order_Multiple: 1 EA
Utilization_Rate: 95%  (47.5/50)
Waste_per_Unit: 2.5 M (5%)
Waste_Cost_Impact: $12.50
Requires_Review: TRUE
Review_Reason: "Engineering length exceeds standard package"
Procurement_Action_Required: "Evaluate suppliers, cut-to-length, or redesign"
```
## Detection Logic / Business Rules
### Rule 1: Dimensional Type Mismatch
```
IF Engineering_Dimension_Type = "CONTINUOUS"
   (Length, Area, Volume, Mass, Time)
AND Procurement_UOM = "EA" or "PC" or "BX" or "SET"
   (Discrete count units)
THEN
   UOM_Conflict_Type = "DIMENSIONAL"
   Requires_Review = TRUE
```
### Rule 2: Requirement Exceeds Package Size
```
IF Engineering_Quantity > Procurement_Package_Size
THEN
   UOM_Conflict_Type = "DIMENSIONAL"
   Multi_Package_Required = TRUE
   Requires_Review = TRUE
   Alert_Engineering = TRUE
   Alert_Message = "Length requirement exceeds standard package size"
```
### Rule 3: High Waste Threshold
```
IF Waste_per_Unit > [Threshold, e.g., 10% or $50]
THEN
   Requires_Review = TRUE
   Alert_Finance = TRUE
   Review_Reason = "Material waste exceeds acceptable threshold"
```
## Item Master Configuration Examples
### Example 1: Cable with Conflict (Your Scenario)
```
PART: CAB-012847-00
Description: Cable Assembly, Power, 47.5M
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

ENGINEERING SPECIFICATION:
  Make_Buy_Code: MAKE (fabricated)
  Engineering_UOM: M
  Quantity_Required: 47.5
  Dimension_Type: LENGTH_CONTINUOUS
  
PROCUREMENT PLANNING:
  Source_Material: CAB-RAW-001 (bulk cable stock)
  UOM_Conflict_Type: DIMENSIONAL 🚨
  
  Engineering_UOM: M (continuous)
  Procurement_UOM: EA (discrete spools)
  Package_Contains: 50 M
  
  Requires_Review: TRUE
  Review_Status: APPROVED
  Review_Date: 2024-08-22
  Review_By: M.Chen (Procurement)
  Review_Notes: "Approved to purchase 50M spools. 
                 2.5M waste per assembly acceptable.
                 Evaluated cut-to-length - not cost effective 
                 at current volumes."
  
  Alternative_Evaluated: Cut-to-length service
  Alternative_Cost: $8.50/M vs. $5/M standard
  Alternative_Decision: REJECTED (68% cost increase)
  
  Utilization: 95%
  Waste_Length: 2.5 M
  Waste_Cost: $12.50
  Annual_Waste_Cost: $6,250 (500 units/year)
```

### Example 2: Fastener - No Conflict
```
PART: BOLT-012345-00
Description: Bolt, Hex Head, M6x20, Grade 8.8
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

ENGINEERING SPECIFICATION:
  Make_Buy_Code: BUY
  Engineering_UOM: EA
  Quantity_Required: 8
  Dimension_Type: COUNT_DISCRETE
  
PROCUREMENT PLANNING:
  UOM_Conflict_Type: NONE ✓
  
  Engineering_UOM: EA (discrete)
  Procurement_UOM: BX (box)
  Package_Contains: 100 EA
  
  Requires_Review: FALSE
  Conversion_Rule: ROUND_UP
  Order_Calculation: CEILING(Qty_Needed / Package_Size)
  
  For 8 EA needed:
  Order: 1 BX (100 EA)
  Available for 12.5 assemblies
  Standard practice - no review needed
```

### Example 3: Sheet Metal - Dimensional Conflict
```
PART: PANEL-FRT-001
Description: Front Panel, Aluminum, 500x300mm
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

ENGINEERING SPECIFICATION:
  Make_Buy_Code: MAKE (cut from sheet)
  Engineering_UOM: M2 (square meter)
  Quantity_Required: 0.15 M2 (500mm x 300mm)
  Dimension_Type: AREA_CONTINUOUS
  
PROCUREMENT PLANNING:
  Source_Material: AL-SHEET-3MM (aluminum sheet stock)
  UOM_Conflict_Type: DIMENSIONAL 🚨
  
  Engineering_UOM: M2 (continuous area)
  Procurement_UOM: EA (discrete sheets)
  Package_Size: 1.22 M x 2.44 M = 2.977 M2 per sheet
  
  Requires_Review: TRUE
  Review_Status: APPROVED
  
  Nesting_Analysis: TRUE
  Parts_per_Sheet: 19 pieces (with optimization)
  Utilization: 95.5%
  Scrap_per_Sheet: 0.13 M2
  
  Review_Notes: "Nesting study shows 19 parts per sheet.
                 Sheet purchase approved. Manufacturing 
                 to optimize cutting pattern per WI-NEST-001."
```

### Example 4: Wire - Bulk Managed
```
PART: WIRE-22AWG-BLK
Description: Wire, 22AWG, Black, Stranded
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

ENGINEERING SPECIFICATION:
  Make_Buy_Code: BUY
  Engineering_UOM: M
  Quantity_Required: 0.35 M (per assembly)
  Dimension_Type: LENGTH_CONTINUOUS
  
PROCUREMENT PLANNING:
  UOM_Conflict_Type: BULK_MANAGED 📦
  
  Engineering_UOM: M (continuous)
  Procurement_UOM: EA (spool)
  Package_Size: 500 M per spool
  
  Requires_Review: FALSE (standard bulk material)
  
  Inventory_Strategy: BULK_STOCK
  Reorder_Point: 2000 M
  Order_Quantity: 2 EA (1000 M)
  Dispensing_Method: Cut-to-length at issue
  
  Annual_Usage: 8,750 M (25,000 assemblies)
  Stock_Turns: 4.4 per year
  
  Review_Notes: "Standard bulk material. Warehouse 
                 cuts to length per kit. No procurement 
                 review required for individual assemblies."
```

## Workflow Triggers
### When Item is Created/Modified
```
TRIGGER: Item save with Make_Buy = "MAKE"
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

CHECK:
1. Does item have source material defined?
2. Compare Engineering_UOM to Source_Procurement_UOM
3. Compare Engineering_Qty to Source_Package_Size
IF conflict detected:
  └─ Set UOM_Conflict_Type
  └─ Set Requires_Review = TRUE
  └─ Create task for Procurement review
  └─ Send notification to Procurement team
  └─ Block item from "Released" status until reviewed

IF no conflict:
  └─ Set UOM_Conflict_Type = "NONE"
  └─ Set Requires_Review = FALSE
  └─ Allow normal workflow
```

### Procurement Review Workflow
```
NOTIFICATION TO PROCUREMENT:
─────────────────────────────────────────────────

Subject: New item requires UOM conflict review
Item: CAB-012847-00
Description: Cable Assembly, Power, 47.5M
Conflict Type: DIMENSIONAL
Engineering needs: 47.5 M
Source material: CAB-RAW-001 (50M spools)
Estimated waste: 2.5 M (5%, $12.50 per unit)
Annual impact: $6,250 (est. 500 units/year)
ACTION REQUIRED:
[ ] Approve standard packaging (accept waste)
[ ] Request cut-to-length quotes
[ ] Recommend design change to Engineering
[ ] Identify alternative suppliers
[ ] Establish bulk purchasing + cutting
APPROVAL FORM:
Decision: _______________
Justification: _______________
Alternatives Evaluated: _______________
Approved By: _______________
Date: _______________
[Approve] [Request Engineering Review] [Need More Info]
```
